<h3>2.2 Tiered Audience Building Strategy</h3>
<p><strong>Tier 1: Cold Start Phase — Broad Targeting + Interest Testing</strong></p>
<p>During the initial launch phase for new accounts or products, use <strong>broad targeting</strong> with 1-2 core interest tags to rapidly accumulate data and identify high-converting audience characteristics. Budget for this phase should be <strong>20%-30%</strong> of total.</p>
<p><strong>Tier 2: Optimization Phase — Lookalikes + Interest Segmentation</strong></p>
<p>Create <strong>1%-3% Lookalike audiences</strong> based on Tier 1 converted users, while conducting segmented testing on well-performing interest categories. Start Lookalike audience testing from 1% and gradually expand to 5%.</p>
<p><strong>Tier 3: Scale Phase — Remarketing + Remarketing Lookalikes</strong></p>
<p>When CPA stabilizes, increase investment in <strong>website visitor remarketing</strong> and <strong>high-value customer Lookalikes</strong>. This audience typically achieves <strong>2-3x higher conversion rates</strong> than pure new customers.</p>
<h3>2.3 Warning Signs: Common Targeting Mistakes</h3>
<blockquote>
<p>⚠️ <strong>Mistake 1: Targeting Too Narrow</strong><br />
Stacking multiple dimensions like age, gender, location, interests, and devices simultaneously results in an audience too small for the algorithm to effectively learn and optimize.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 2: Not Excluding Converted Users</strong><br />
Failing to exclude "purchased users" leads to repeated ad exposure to already-converted audiences, wasting budget.</p>
<p><strong>Mistake 3: Oversized Lookalike Audiences</strong><br />
Creating 10% Lookalike audiences provides scale but low similarity to seed users, resulting in poor conversion quality.</p>
</blockquote>
